## Appendix B ProjDiff for VE diffusion

In this section, we derive the ProjDiff algorithm for the Variance Exploding (VE) diffusion used in the source separation and partial generation tasks. The experiments using VE diffusion in this work are all noise-free, thus we only focus on the noise-free scenarios and leave the noisy scenarios of VE diffusion for future work.

Consider the forward transition probability \(q(\mathbf{x}_{t}|\mathbf{x}_{t-1})=\mathcal{N}(\mathbf{x}_{t};\mathbf{x}_{t- 1},(\overline{\sigma}_{t}^{2}-\overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^{2})\mathbf{I})\), with \(\overline{\sigma}_{T}>\overline{\sigma}_{T-1}>\cdots>\overline{\sigma}_{1}> \overline{\sigma}_{0}\to 0\). When \(\overline{\sigma}_{T}\) is large enough, \(q(\mathbf{x}_{T})\approx\mathcal{N}(\mathbf{0},\sigma_{T}^{2}\mathbf{I})\). The initial distribution of the reverse process is set to be \(p_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{T})=\mathcal{N}(\mathbf{0},\sigma_{T}^{2}\mathbf{ I})\approx q(\mathbf{x}_{T})\) and the reverse transition in the DDPM manner is

\[p_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{t-1}|\mathbf{x}_{t})=\mathcal{N}\left(\mathbf{x}_ {t-1};\bm{\mu}_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{t},t)+\frac{\overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^ {2}}{\overline{\sigma}_{t}^{2}}(\mathbf{x}_{t}-\bm{\mu}_{\bm{\theta}}( \mathbf{x}_{t},t)),\frac{\overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^{2}(\overline{\sigma}_{t}^ {2}-\overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^{2})}{\overline{\sigma}_{t}^{2}}\mathbf{I}\right),\] (58)

for \(t\geq 2\), which matches the condition probability

\[q(\mathbf{x}_{t-1}|\mathbf{x}_{t},\mathbf{x}_{0})=\mathcal{N}\left(\mathbf{x} _{t-1};\mathbf{x}_{0}+\frac{\overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^{2}}{\overline{\sigma}_{ t}^{2}}(\mathbf{x}_{t}-\mathbf{x}_{0}),\frac{\overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^{2}( \overline{\sigma}_{t}^{2}-\overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^{2})}{\overline{\sigma}_{t }^{2}}\mathbf{I}\right).\] (59)

And we assume the last sampling step is set to be

\[p_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{0}|\mathbf{x}_{1})=\mathcal{N}(\mathbf{x}_{0};\bm {\mu}_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{1},1),\delta_{0}^{2}\mathbf{I}),\] (60)

for some small \(\delta_{0}\).

Thus the ELBO is derived as the same in DDPM [2].

\[\log p_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{0})= \log\int_{t=1}^{T}p_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{0:T})\frac{q( \mathbf{x}_{1:T}|\mathbf{x}_{0})}{q(\mathbf{x}_{1:T}|\mathbf{x}_{0})}\mathbf{ dx}_{1:T}\] (61) \[\geq c-D_{KL}(q(\mathbf{x}_{T}|\mathbf{x}_{0})||p_{\bm{\theta}}( \mathbf{x}_{T}))+\mathbb{E}_{q(\mathbf{x}_{1}|\mathbf{x}_{0})}\log p_{\bm{ \theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{0}|\mathbf{x}_{1})\] \[-\sum_{t=2}^{T}\mathbb{E}_{q(\mathbf{x}_{t}|\mathbf{x}_{0})}D_{KL} (q(\mathbf{x}_{t-1}|\mathbf{x}_{t},\mathbf{x}_{0})||p_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x} _{t-1}|\mathbf{x}_{t})).\]

\(D_{KL}(q(\mathbf{x}_{T}|\mathbf{x}_{0})||p_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{T})) \approx 0\), and \(\log p_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{0}|\mathbf{x}_{1})=c_{1}-\frac{1}{2\delta_{0} ^{2}}||\mathbf{x}_{0}-\bm{\mu}_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{1},1)||^{2}\). The KL divergence between \(q(\mathbf{x}_{t-1}|\mathbf{x}_{t},\mathbf{x}_{0})\) and \(p_{\theta}(\mathbf{x}_{t-1}|\mathbf{x}_{t})\) is

\[D_{KL}(q(\mathbf{x}_{t-1}|\mathbf{x}_{t},\mathbf{x}_{0})|p_{\bm{\theta}}( \mathbf{x}_{t-1}|\mathbf{x}_{t}))=c_{2}+\frac{\overline{\sigma}_{t}^{2}- \overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^{2}}{2\overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^{2}}||\mathbf{x}_{0}- \bm{\mu}_{\bm{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{t},t)||^{2},\] (62)for \(t\geq 2\). Then by reparameterization, we get the Evidence Lower Bound as

\[\text{ELBO}_{\text{VE}}=C-\sum_{t=1}^{T}s(t)\mathbb{E}_{\bm{\epsilon}\sim\mathcal{ N}(\mathbf{0},\mathbf{I})}||\mathbf{x}_{0}-\bm{\mu_{\theta}}(\mathbf{x}_{0}+ \overline{\sigma}_{t}\bm{\epsilon},t)||^{2},\] (63)

with

\[s(t)=\begin{cases}\frac{1}{2\delta_{t}^{2}}&t=1;\\ \frac{\overline{\sigma}_{t}^{2}-\overline{\sigma}_{t-1}^{2}}{2\overline{\sigma }_{t-1}^{2}\overline{\sigma}_{t}^{2}}&2\leq t\leq T.\end{cases}\] (64)

Sampling \(t\sim\mathcal{U}\left\{1,2,\ldots,T\right\}\), \(\bm{\epsilon}\sim\mathcal{N}(\mathbf{0},\mathbf{I})\), and truncating the gradient through \(\bm{\mu_{\theta}}\) as in the VP setting, a stochastic gradient for \(-\text{ELBO}_{\text{VE}}\) (for minimization) is

\[\tilde{\mathbf{d}}_{\mathbf{x}_{0},t}=\mathbf{x}_{0}-\bm{\mu_{\theta}}( \mathbf{x}_{0}+\overline{\sigma}_{t}\bm{\epsilon},t).\] (65)

Then the iteration step of the ProjDiff (noise-free) in the VE setting is

\[\text{(ProjDiff for VE)}\ \mathbf{x}_{0}\leftarrow\mathcal{P}_{\mathbf{A}, \mathcal{Y}}\left(\mathbf{x}_{0}-\eta\tilde{\mathbf{d}}_{\mathbf{x}_{0},t} \right),\] (66)

where \(\eta\) is the step size.

